Female genitalia
(
Fig. 82
) with an oval, membranous, corpus bursae (twice as large as in 

R. auctata

); ductus bursae chitinized, funnel-shaped towards ovipositor (its anterior part much narrower than that in 

R. auctata

, see 
Fig. 81
).
